    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>By Mr. BURGESS:H.R. 4036.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Under Article 1, Section VIII, Clause 1, ``The Congressshall have power to lay and collect taxes, duties, impostsand excises, to pay the debts and provide for the commondefense and general welfare of the United States . . .'' Inaddition, Article I, Section VIII, Clause 14 provides, ``Tomake rules for the government and regulation of the land andnaval forces.'' Lastly, Article I, Section VIII, Clause 16states ``The Congress shall have Power To provide fororganizing, arming, and disciplining, the Militia, and forgoverning such Part of them as may be employed in the Serviceof the United States, reserving to the States respectively,the Appointment of the Officers, and the Authority oftraining the Militia according to the discipline prescribedby Congress.''[Page H1771]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
